{
  "manifest": 3,
  "name": "GitHub Issues",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "icon": "🐙",
  "description": "Pulls open issues from a GitHub repo on a schedule into a review queue — add them to the board yourself, or let the addon's customizable triage agent decide which become tasks. Uses a keychain-stored token for private repos.",
  "author": "yaam",
  "hosts": [
    "api.github.com"
  ],
  "secrets": [
    {
      "name": "GITHUB_TOKEN",
      "label": "GitHub personal access token (repo read scope; optional for public repos)"
    }
  ],
  "permissions": [
    "state:read",
    "tasks",
    "schedules",
    "storage",
    "ui",
    "http",
    "secrets",
    "agent"
  ],
  "hooks": {
    "onCronFired": "// (input = { name, kind }, api) — sync new GitHub issues when our schedule\n// fires. New (unseen) open issues land in the review queue; in auto mode the\n// triage agent is woken with them instead and decides which become tasks.\nif (input.name !== 'github-issues-sync') return\n\nconst cfg = (await api.storage.get('config')) || {}\nif (!cfg.owner || !cfg.repo) return\n\n// only send the Authorization header when a token is actually stored —\n// {{secret:…}} on an unset secret is a hard error by design\nconst secrets = await api.secrets.list()\nconst hasToken = secrets.some(s => s.name === 'GITHUB_TOKEN' && s.set)\nconst headers = { accept: 'application/vnd.github+json' }\nif (hasToken) headers.authorization = 'Bearer {{secret:GITHUB_TOKEN}}'\n\nconst labels = cfg.labels ? '&labels=' + encodeURIComponent(cfg.labels) : ''\nconst res = await api.http.request('GET',\n  `https://api.github.com/repos/${cfg.owner}/${cfg.repo}/issues?state=open&per_page=50&sort=created&direction=desc${labels}`,\n  { headers })\nif (res.status !== 200) {\n  await api.logEvent(`GitHub sync failed: HTTP ${res.status}`)\n  return\n}\n\nconst seen = (await api.storage.get('seen')) || []\nconst queue = (await api.storage.get('queue')) || []\nconst fresh = JSON.parse(res.text)\n  .filter(i => !i.pull_request) // the issues endpoint returns PRs too\n  .filter(i => !seen.includes(i.number) && !queue.some(q => q.number === i.number))\n  .map(i => ({\n    number: i.number,\n    title: i.title,\n    body: (i.body || '').slice(0, 2000),\n    labels: (i.labels || []).map(l => l.name),\n    url: i.html_url,\n    at: Date.now(),\n  }))\n\nawait api.storage.set('lastSync', { at: Date.now(), found: fresh.length, status: res.status })\nif (!fresh.length) return\n\nawait api.storage.set('queue', [...queue, ...fresh].slice(-100))\n\nif (cfg.auto) {\n  // auto mode: the triage agent reads the batch and files board tasks per its\n  // instructions (customize them in this addon's chat)\n  await api.agent.wake('New GitHub issues arrived — triage them per your instructions:\\n\\n'\n    + JSON.stringify(fresh.map(f => ({ number: f.number, title: f.title, labels: f.labels, body: f.body.slice(0, 400) })), null, 2))\n} else {\n  await api.notify('GitHub Issues', `${fresh.length} new issue(s) queued — review them in the GitHub Issues tab`)\n}\n"
  },
  "agent": {
    "system": "You are the triage officer for a GitHub-issues → task-board pipeline. When woken with a batch of new issues (JSON), decide for each one whether it becomes a board task.\n\nDefault policy (the user can refine this in the addon's Customize chat):\n- File a task for concrete, actionable issues: bugs with reproduction details, small well-scoped features, chores.\n- Skip questions, discussions, duplicates of queued/board work (check get_state first), and anything labelled `wontfix`, `duplicate`, or `question`.\n\nFor each issue you accept:\n1. Create the task with add_task — title `#<number> · <issue title>`, the issue body (plus its URL) as the description, and 1-3 verifiable acceptance criteria you derive from the issue. Use the `cwd` from storage key `config` (field `cwd`) when set. Do NOT start tasks yourself unless storage `config.autostart` is true.\n2. Remove the issue from the storage `queue` (match by `number`) and append its number to storage `seen`.\n\nFor each issue you skip: also move its number from `queue` to `seen`, and keep a one-line reason in storage `triageLog` (array, newest first, cap 50).\n\nFinish with a short summary: how many filed, how many skipped, why.\n"
  },
  "html": "<!DOCTYPE html><html><head><style>\n:root{--bg:#0A0B0F;--panel:#12151C;--panel2:#0D0F14;--line:#1a1e26;--line2:#23272F;--text:#E7E9F0;--mut:#8B93A1;--dim:#5a6170;--acc:#F5C451;--green:#3DDC97;--red:#FF5C5C;--amber:#FFB020}\n*{box-sizing:border-box}\nbody{margin:0;background:var(--bg);color:var(--text);font-family:'IBM Plex Sans',system-ui,sans-serif;padding:24px;max-width:880px;font-size:13px}\n.mono{font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace}\nh1{font-size:15px;margin:0;display:flex;gap:9px;align-items:center}\nh2{font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.6px;color:var(--dim);margin:24px 0 8px;text-transform:uppercase;font-weight:600;display:flex;gap:8px;align-items:baseline}\n.card{background:var(--panel);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:11px;padding:13px 15px;margin-bottom:8px}\n.row{display:flex;gap:9px;align-items:center;flex-wrap:wrap}\ninput,select{background:var(--bg);border:1px solid var(--line2);border-radius:8px;color:var(--text);font-size:11.5px;padding:6px 9px;outline:none;font-family:inherit}\ninput:focus{border-color:rgba(245,196,81,.45)}\nbutton{background:transparent;border:1px solid var(--line2);border-radius:8px;color:var(--text);font-size:11.5px;padding:6px 13px;cursor:pointer;font-family:inherit;transition:all .12s}\nbutton:hover{border-color:var(--acc);color:var(--acc)}\nbutton:disabled{opacity:.4;cursor:default;pointer-events:none}\nbutton.primary{border-color:rgba(61,220,151,.45);color:var(--green)}\nbutton.primary:hover{background:rgba(61,220,151,.08)}\nbutton.ghost{border-color:transparent;color:var(--mut);padding:6px 8px}\nbutton.ghost:hover{color:var(--red)}\nlabel.f{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:3px;font-size:9.5px;color:var(--dim);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.4px;font-weight:600}\n.chk{display:flex;gap:7px;align-items:center;font-size:11.5px;color:var(--mut);cursor:pointer}\n.chk input{width:auto;accent-color:var(--acc)}\n.dot{width:7px;height:7px;border-radius:50%;display:inline-block;margin-right:6px;background:var(--line2);flex:none}\n.dot.on{background:var(--green)}\n.dot.amber{background:var(--amber)}\n.chip{font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:10px;color:var(--mut);border:1px solid var(--line2);border-radius:6px;padding:2px 9px}\n.chip b{color:var(--text)}\n.stepnum{width:19px;height:19px;border-radius:50%;border:1px solid var(--line2);color:var(--dim);font-size:10.5px;display:inline-flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex:none}\n.step-done .stepnum{border-color:rgba(61,220,151,.5);color:var(--green)}\n.step-done .stept{color:var(--dim);text-decoration:line-through}\n.stept{font-size:12px}\n.iss{display:flex;gap:12px;align-items:flex-start}\n.iss .num{font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;color:var(--acc);font-size:11.5px;padding-top:2px;flex:none}\n.iss b{font-size:12.5px;cursor:pointer}\n.iss .body{font-size:11.5px;color:var(--mut);margin-top:4px;line-height:1.5;max-height:52px;overflow:hidden;transition:max-height .15s}\n.iss.open .body{max-height:400px;overflow-y:auto}\n.lbl{font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:9px;border-radius:4px;padding:1px 6px;margin-left:6px;border:1px solid}\n.meta{font-family:'JetBrains Mono',monospace;font-size:10px;color:var(--dim);margin-top:5px}\na{color:var(--acc);text-decoration:none}\n.empty{color:var(--dim);font-size:12px;padding:8px 2px}\n#banner{display:none;background:rgba(255,92,92,.08);border:1px solid rgba(255,92,92,.3);color:var(--red);font-size:11.5px;padding:8px 12px;border-radius:9px;margin:10px 0}\n.callout{background:var(--panel2);border:1px dashed var(--line2);border-radius:9px;padding:9px 12px;font-size:11.5px;color:var(--mut);line-height:1.55}\n@keyframes spin{to{transform:rotate(360deg)}}\n.spin{display:inline-block;animation:spin .8s linear infinite}\n</style></head><body>\n<div class=\"row\">\n  <h1>🐙 GitHub Issues</h1>\n  <span id=\"repoChip\" class=\"chip\" style=\"display:none\"></span>\n  <span style=\"flex:1\"></span>\n  <span id=\"stats\" class=\"row\"></span>\n</div>\n<div style=\"font-size:11.5px;color:var(--dim);margin-top:4px\">open issues → review queue → board tasks · synced on a schedule, token stays in the OS keychain</div>\n<div id=\"banner\"></div>\n\n<div id=\"setup\"></div>\n\n<h2>Configuration</h2>\n<div class=\"card\">\n  <div class=\"row\">\n    <label class=\"f\">owner<input id=\"owner\" placeholder=\"anthropics\" style=\"width:130px\"></label>\n    <label class=\"f\">repository<input id=\"repo\" placeholder=\"claude-code\" style=\"width:160px\"></label>\n    <label class=\"f\">labels filter<input id=\"labels\" placeholder=\"bug,help wanted\" style=\"width:150px\"></label>\n    <label class=\"f\" style=\"flex:1;min-width:170px\">workdir for created tasks<input id=\"cwd\" placeholder=\"(workspace default)\"></label>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"row\" style=\"margin-top:12px\">\n    <span class=\"mono\" style=\"font-size:10.5px;color:var(--mut)\"><span id=\"tokDot\" class=\"dot\"></span><span id=\"tokTxt\">checking token…</span></span>\n    <span style=\"flex:1\"></span>\n    <button class=\"primary\" onclick=\"saveCfg(true)\">Save</button>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Sync</h2>\n<div class=\"card row\">\n  <button id=\"schedBtn\" onclick=\"toggleSchedule()\">…</button>\n  <select id=\"interval\" style=\"width:120px\">\n    <option value=\"*/15 * * * *\">every 15 min</option>\n    <option value=\"*/30 * * * *\" selected>every 30 min</option>\n    <option value=\"0 * * * *\">hourly</option>\n  </select>\n  <span id=\"lastSync\" class=\"mono\" style=\"font-size:10.5px;color:var(--dim)\"></span>\n  <span style=\"flex:1\"></span>\n  <button id=\"syncBtn\" onclick=\"syncNow()\">⟳ Sync now</button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"card row\">\n  <label class=\"chk\"><input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"auto\" onchange=\"saveCfg()\"> <span><b>auto-triage</b> — the addon's agent reviews new issues and files the tasks itself</span></label>\n  <label class=\"chk\"><input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"autostart\" onchange=\"saveCfg()\"> agent may also start them</label>\n</div>\n<div id=\"autoNote\" class=\"callout\" style=\"display:none\">\n  Auto-triage uses this addon's own agent. Its policy (which issues become tasks, how criteria are written) is plain\n  instructions — open the addon's <b>Customize</b> chat to change it, e.g. “only file issues labelled bug”.\n</div>\n\n<h2>Queue <span id=\"qCount\" class=\"mono\" style=\"color:var(--dim);letter-spacing:0;text-transform:none\"></span>\n  <span style=\"flex:1\"></span><button class=\"ghost\" id=\"clearQ\" onclick=\"dismissAll()\" style=\"display:none;font-size:10.5px\">dismiss all</button></h2>\n<div id=\"queue\"></div>\n\n<h2>Agent triage log</h2>\n<div id=\"tri\" class=\"card mono\" style=\"max-height:140px;overflow-y:auto;font-size:10.5px;color:var(--mut);line-height:1.7\"></div>\n\n<script>\n'use strict'\nlet seq = 0\nconst pending = {}\nfunction call(method, ...args){\n  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {\n    const callId = 'c' + (++seq)\n    pending[callId] = { resolve, reject }\n    parent.postMessage({ type: 'yaam:call', callId, method, args }, '*')\n  })\n}\nwindow.addEventListener('message', e => {\n  const d = e.data\n  if (d && d.type === 'yaam:result' && pending[d.callId]) {\n    d.error ? pending[d.callId].reject(new Error(d.error)) : pending[d.callId].resolve(d.result)\n    delete pending[d.callId]\n  }\n  if (d && d.type === 'yaam:state') refresh()\n})\nfunction banner(msg){\n  const b = document.getElementById('banner')\n  if (!msg) { b.style.display = 'none'; return }\n  b.textContent = /permission \"/.test(msg) ? msg + ' — grant it in the Addons view, then retry.' : msg\n  b.style.display = 'block'\n  setTimeout(() => { b.style.display = 'none' }, 7000)\n}\nconst esc = t => String(t == null ? '' : t).replace(/[&<>\"]/g, c => ({'&':'&amp;','<':'&lt;','>':'&gt;','\"':'&quot;'}[c]))\nconst ago = t => { const s = (Date.now() - t) / 1000; return s < 90 ? 'just now' : s < 3600 ? Math.round(s / 60) + 'm ago' : s < 86400 ? Math.round(s / 3600) + 'h ago' : Math.round(s / 86400) + 'd ago' }\n// deterministic label color from its name\nfunction lblColor(name){\n  let h = 0\n  for (let i = 0; i < name.length; i++) h = (h * 31 + name.charCodeAt(i)) % 360\n  return `hsl(${h},55%,68%)`\n}\n\nlet cfg = {}, tokenSet = false, openIssue = null\nasync function load(){\n  try { cfg = (await call('storage.get', 'config')) || {} } catch (e) { banner(e.message) }\n  document.getElementById('owner').value = cfg.owner || ''\n  document.getElementById('repo').value = cfg.repo || ''\n  document.getElementById('labels').value = cfg.labels || ''\n  document.getElementById('cwd').value = cfg.cwd || ''\n  document.getElementById('auto').checked = !!cfg.auto\n  document.getElementById('autostart').checked = !!cfg.autostart\n  if (cfg.interval) document.getElementById('interval').value = cfg.interval\n  try {\n    const secrets = await call('secrets.list')\n    const tok = secrets.find(s => s.name === 'GITHUB_TOKEN')\n    tokenSet = !!(tok && tok.set)\n    document.getElementById('tokDot').className = 'dot' + (tokenSet ? ' on' : ' amber')\n    document.getElementById('tokTxt').textContent = tokenSet ? 'GITHUB_TOKEN set — private repos ok' : 'no token — public repos only (set it in the Addons view)'\n  } catch (e) {\n    document.getElementById('tokTxt').textContent = 'grant the \"secrets\" scope to use a token'\n  }\n  paintShell()\n  refresh()\n}\nfunction paintShell(){\n  const chip = document.getElementById('repoChip')\n  if (cfg.owner && cfg.repo) {\n    chip.style.display = ''\n    chip.innerHTML = `<b>${esc(cfg.owner)}/${esc(cfg.repo)}</b>${cfg.labels ? ' · ' + esc(cfg.labels) : ''}`\n  } else chip.style.display = 'none'\n  const sb = document.getElementById('schedBtn')\n  sb.textContent = cfg.schedOn ? '✓ Scheduled' : 'Enable schedule'\n  sb.className = cfg.schedOn ? 'primary' : ''\n  document.getElementById('autoNote').style.display = cfg.auto ? '' : 'none'\n  // onboarding checklist until the pipeline is fully armed\n  const steps = [\n    ['Point at a repository (owner + repo, Save)', !!(cfg.owner && cfg.repo)],\n    ['Optional: store GITHUB_TOKEN in the Addons view for private repos', tokenSet],\n    ['Enable the schedule (or hit Sync now)', !!cfg.schedOn],\n  ]\n  const el = document.getElementById('setup')\n  el.innerHTML = steps.every(s => s[1]) ? '' : '<div class=\"card\">' + steps.map((s, i) =>\n    `<div class=\"row${s[1] ? ' step-done' : ''}\" style=\"padding:3px 0\"><span class=\"stepnum\">${s[1] ? '✓' : i + 1}</span><span class=\"stept\">${s[0]}</span></div>`).join('') + '</div>'\n}\nasync function saveCfg(flash){\n  cfg = { ...cfg,\n    owner: document.getElementById('owner').value.trim(),\n    repo: document.getElementById('repo').value.trim(),\n    labels: document.getElementById('labels').value.trim(),\n    cwd: document.getElementById('cwd').value.trim(),\n    auto: document.getElementById('auto').checked,\n    autostart: document.getElementById('autostart').checked,\n    interval: document.getElementById('interval').value,\n  }\n  try { await call('storage.set', 'config', cfg) } catch (e) { banner(e.message); return }\n  if (flash) call('flash', 'saved')\n  paintShell()\n}\nasync function toggleSchedule(){\n  try {\n    if (cfg.schedOn) {\n      await call('schedules.remove', 'github-issues-sync')\n      cfg.schedOn = false\n    } else {\n      await saveCfg()\n      if (!cfg.owner || !cfg.repo) { banner('point at a repository first'); return }\n      await call('schedules.add', { name: 'github-issues-sync', schedule: cfg.interval || '*/30 * * * *' })\n      cfg.schedOn = true\n    }\n    await call('storage.set', 'config', cfg)\n  } catch (e) { banner(e.message); return }\n  paintShell()\n}\n\nasync function syncNow(){\n  await saveCfg()\n  if (!cfg.owner || !cfg.repo) { banner('point at a repository first'); return }\n  const btn = document.getElementById('syncBtn')\n  btn.disabled = true\n  btn.innerHTML = '<span class=\"spin\">⟳</span> Syncing…'\n  try {\n    let headers = { accept: 'application/vnd.github+json' }\n    try {\n      const secrets = await call('secrets.list')\n      if (secrets.some(s => s.name === 'GITHUB_TOKEN' && s.set)) headers.authorization = 'Bearer {{secret:GITHUB_TOKEN}}'\n    } catch (e) { /* secrets scope not granted — try anonymously */ }\n    const labels = cfg.labels ? '&labels=' + encodeURIComponent(cfg.labels) : ''\n    const res = await call('http.request', 'GET',\n      'https://api.github.com/repos/' + cfg.owner + '/' + cfg.repo + '/issues?state=open&per_page=50&sort=created&direction=desc' + labels,\n      { headers })\n    if (res.status === 404) throw new Error('repo not found (private without a token?)')\n    if (res.status !== 200) throw new Error('GitHub replied HTTP ' + res.status)\n    const seen = (await call('storage.get', 'seen')) || []\n    const queue = (await call('storage.get', 'queue')) || []\n    const fresh = JSON.parse(res.text)\n      .filter(i => !i.pull_request)\n      .filter(i => seen.indexOf(i.number) === -1 && !queue.some(q => q.number === i.number))\n      .map(i => ({ number: i.number, title: i.title, body: (i.body || '').slice(0, 2000), labels: (i.labels || []).map(l => l.name), url: i.html_url, at: Date.now() }))\n    await call('storage.set', 'queue', queue.concat(fresh).slice(-100))\n    await call('storage.set', 'lastSync', { at: Date.now(), found: fresh.length, status: res.status })\n    await call('flash', fresh.length ? fresh.length + ' new issue(s) queued' : 'no new issues')\n    if (fresh.length && cfg.auto) {\n      await call('agent.wake', 'New GitHub issues arrived — triage them per your instructions:\\n\\n'\n        + JSON.stringify(fresh.map(f => ({ number: f.number, title: f.title, labels: f.labels, body: f.body.slice(0, 400) })), null, 2))\n    }\n  } catch (e) { banner(e.message) }\n  btn.disabled = false\n  btn.innerHTML = '⟳ Sync now'\n  refresh()\n}\n\nasync function addToBoard(number, btn){\n  if (btn) { btn.disabled = true; btn.textContent = 'adding…' }\n  try {\n    const queue = (await call('storage.get', 'queue')) || []\n    const it = queue.find(q => q.number === number)\n    if (!it) return\n    await call('tasks.add', ('#' + it.number + ' · ' + it.title).slice(0, 120), 'backlog', {\n      description: it.body + '\\n\\n' + it.url,\n      cwd: cfg.cwd || undefined,\n    })\n    await markSeen(number)\n    await call('flash', 'task filed for #' + number)\n  } catch (e) { banner(e.message) }\n  refresh()\n}\nasync function markSeen(number){\n  const queue = (await call('storage.get', 'queue')) || []\n  const seen = (await call('storage.get', 'seen')) || []\n  await call('storage.set', 'queue', queue.filter(q => q.number !== number))\n  if (seen.indexOf(number) === -1) await call('storage.set', 'seen', seen.concat([number]).slice(-500))\n}\nasync function dismiss(number){ try { await markSeen(number) } catch (e) { banner(e.message) } refresh() }\nasync function dismissAll(){\n  try {\n    const queue = (await call('storage.get', 'queue')) || []\n    const seen = (await call('storage.get', 'seen')) || []\n    await call('storage.set', 'seen', seen.concat(queue.map(q => q.number)).slice(-500))\n    await call('storage.set', 'queue', [])\n  } catch (e) { banner(e.message) }\n  refresh()\n}\n\nasync function refresh(){\n  let queue = [], seen = [], last = null, tri = []\n  try {\n    queue = (await call('storage.get', 'queue')) || []\n    seen = (await call('storage.get', 'seen')) || []\n    last = await call('storage.get', 'lastSync')\n    tri = (await call('storage.get', 'triageLog')) || []\n  } catch (e) { return }\n  document.getElementById('stats').innerHTML =\n    `<span class=\"chip\"><b>${queue.length}</b> queued</span><span class=\"chip\"><b>${seen.length}</b> handled</span>`\n  document.getElementById('qCount').textContent = queue.length ? '· ' + queue.length : ''\n  document.getElementById('clearQ').style.display = queue.length > 1 ? '' : 'none'\n  document.getElementById('lastSync').textContent = last ? 'last sync ' + ago(last.at) + ' · +' + last.found : 'never synced'\n  const el = document.getElementById('queue')\n  el.innerHTML = ''\n  for (const it of queue.slice().reverse()) {\n    const d = document.createElement('div')\n    d.className = 'card iss' + (openIssue === it.number ? ' open' : '')\n    const labels = it.labels.map(l => { const c = lblColor(l); return `<span class=\"lbl\" style=\"color:${c};border-color:${c}44\">${esc(l)}</span>` }).join('')\n    d.innerHTML = `<span class=\"num\">#${it.number}</span><div style=\"flex:1;min-width:0\">`\n      + `<b onclick=\"toggleIssue(${it.number})\">${esc(it.title)}</b>${labels}`\n      + `<div class=\"body\">${esc(it.body) || '<i>no description</i>'}</div>`\n      + `<div class=\"meta\">queued ${ago(it.at)} · <a href=\"${esc(it.url)}\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">open on GitHub ↗</a></div></div>`\n    const col = document.createElement('div')\n    col.style.cssText = 'display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:5px;flex:none'\n    const add = document.createElement('button'); add.className = 'primary'; add.textContent = '＋ Add to board'; add.onclick = () => addToBoard(it.number, add)\n    const dis = document.createElement('button'); dis.className = 'ghost'; dis.textContent = 'dismiss'; dis.onclick = () => dismiss(it.number)\n    col.appendChild(add); col.appendChild(dis)\n    d.appendChild(col)\n    el.appendChild(d)\n  }\n  if (!queue.length) el.innerHTML = '<div class=\"empty\">queue is empty — enable the schedule or hit ⟳ Sync now</div>'\n  document.getElementById('tri').innerHTML = tri.length ? tri.map(t => '<div>' + esc(t) + '</div>').join('') : '<span class=\"empty\">the agent has not triaged anything yet — turn on auto-triage above</span>'\n}\nfunction toggleIssue(n){ openIssue = openIssue === n ? null : n; refresh() }\nload()\nparent.postMessage({ type: 'yaam:getState' }, '*')\n</script></body></html>\n"
}
